modules.description: Defines a time-based axis configuration for real-time data visualization. It specializes in handling temporal data streams, ensuring proper display of dynamically updating time series. Useful for rendering live sensor data or monitoring metrics in a web interface.

This module enables real-time data visualization by configuring streaming behavior for chart axes, supporting both global and axis-specific settings. It provides operations to create and apply streaming configurations to JavaScript chart objects, with a focus on time-based data handling. The time-based axis submodule specializes in visualizing dynamic temporal streams, such as live sensor readings or monitoring metrics. Together, they allow developers to set up and customize real-time updates directly on chart axes or through global options.
